For `ncat `: the `ncat` is the whole word, so preceded by a boundary (space), and followed by space (already handled by trailing space in pattern).

For `netcat `: same analysis.

So the fix is to, when we find a match of `nc `/`ncat `/`netcat `, also verify that the match starts at a word boundary.

